Question: How can I pass LVS for stacked MIM_Cap over MOS_Cap ?

Answer: The following must be done to pass lvs:

1) on the layout, the tm/mim layer must sit completely inside of the
nwell of the moscap.

2) on the schematic, the mim cap to be used must be c3t_mimw (the well
version); the substrate node of this c3t_mimw must be the same as the
"bottom" plate of the moscap (i.e. the active terminal).

However, the presence of the moscap will invalidate the substrate
coupling model of c3t_mimw. In this case, we cannot guarantee the
accuracy of the substrate coupling model.